'''Enzo Jeremías Fernández''' (born 17 January 2001) is an Argentine professional [[footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|Chelsea}} club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]]. Primarily a [[central midfielder]], he is also capable of playing as a [[Defensive midfielder|defensive]] or [[attacking midfielder]].

As an academy graduate of [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]], Fernández made his first-team debut for the club in 2019, before spending two seasons on loan with [[Defensa y Justicia]]. There, he won the [[Copa Sudamericana]] and [[Recopa Sudamericana]], and returned to River Plate in 2021. He joined [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in the summer of 2022. Having played only six months for them, he joined Chelsea in January 2023 for a [[Progression of the British football transfer fee record|British-record transfer fee]] worth €121&nbsp;million (£106.8&nbsp;million).

An Argentine international, Fernández previously represented his country at [[Argentina national under-18 football team|under-18 level]] before making his senior international debut. He represented Argentina at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], playing an important role in helping his country win their third title, while also winning the tournament's [[FIFA World Cup Young Player Award|Young Player Award]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-16 |title=Argentina World Cup 2022 squad, predicted line-up versus France and star players {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/argentina-2022-world-cup-squad-lionel-messi-angel-di-maria-lautaro-martinez/bltf44827cf3c387dd8#csc503596cf8b68b68 |access-date=2025-04-14 |website=www.goal.com |language=en}}</ref> He also won the [[2024 Copa América]].

==Club career==

===River Plate===

====Early career====
Born in [[San Martín, Buenos Aires]]<!-- DO NOT LINK SEPARATELY, see [[MOS:GEOLINK]] for further guidance -->, to Raúl and Marta; Fernández has four brothers, Seba, Rodri, Maxi and Gonza.<ref name=":0">{{cite web |title=Enzo Fernández: "En River tenés que tener una actitud mental ganadora" |trans-title=Enzo Fernández: 'En River tenés que tener una actitud mental ganadora' |url=https://www.cariverplate.com.ar/enzo-fernandez-en-river-tenes-que-tener-una-actitud-mental-ganadora |access-date=14 April 2025 |publisher=Club Atlético River Plate |language=es}}</ref> He was introduced to football at a young age, playing for a local side called Club La Recova, before joining [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">{{cite web |last=Uria |first=Maximiliano |date=26 September 2020 |title=Enzo Fernández, el juvenil de River que brilla en la Copa Libertadores para Defensa y Justicia |trans-title=Enzo Fernández, the young player from River who shines in the Copa Libertadores for Defensa y Justicia. |url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/enzo-fernandez-juvenil-river-brilla-copa-libertadores-defensa-justicia_0_-B61_VQnB.html |access-date=14 April 2025 |website=Clarín |language=es}}</ref> It is unclear exactly when Fernández joined River Plate; in November 2019, in an interview for the River Plate website, he claimed to have joined the academy in 2005,<ref name=":0" /> in September 2020, Argentine newspaper [[Clarín (Argentine newspaper)|Clarín]] reported that he joined River in 2006,<ref name=":1" /> while in February 2023, he claimed he was six when he joined in an interview for the [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] website, which would have most likely been in 2007.<ref>{{cite news |title=Enzo Fernandez interview – the Argentina years |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/enzo-fernandez-interview-the-argentina-years |date=21 February 2023 |access-date=14 April 2025 |publisher=Chelsea F.C.}}</ref>

He progressed through the youth ranks, and was promoted into the club's first-team by manager [[Marcelo Gallardo]] on 27 January 2019, in a 3–1 home loss to [[Club Atlético Patronato|Patronato]] in the [[Argentine Primera División|Primera División]], despite remaining on the bench.<ref name="SW1">{{cite news |title=Argentina – E. Fernández |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/enzo-jeremias-fernandez/547472/ |access-date=6 April 2025 |work=Soccerway}}</ref> He made his first-team debut on 4 March 2020, replacing [[Santiago Sosa]] in the 75th minute of a 3–0 loss to [[L.D.U. Quito|LDU Quito]] in the [[Copa Libertadores]].<ref name="SW1"/> In the weeks prior, he scored once, in the 6–1 thrashing of [[Club Libertad|Libertad]], in four games at the [[2020 U-20 Copa Libertadores]] in Paraguay.<ref name="SW1"/>

====2020–21: Loan to Defensa y Justicia====
Despite being sporadically used Fernández's manager advised him to leave the club on loan, in order to continue his development.<ref name=":2">{{cite web |title=Enzo Fernández: o “herdeiro” de Francescoli que convence rapidamente |trans-title=Enzo Fernández: the "heir" to Francescoli who wins people over quickly. |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica/transferencias/enzo-fernandez-o-herdeiro-de-francescoli-que-convence-rapidamente |access-date=14 April 2025 |language=es |website=Maisfutebol}}</ref> In August, Fernández was loaned to fellow top-flight club [[Defensa y Justicia]].<ref name="SW1"/><ref name="VAV1">{{cite news |date=4 September 2020 |title=Fernández: "Esta oportunidad que me da Defensa es muy importante" |trans-title=Fernández: "This opportunity that Defensa is giving me is very important." |url=https://www.vavel.com/ar/futbol-argentino/2020/09/04/defensa-y-justicia/1035365-fernandez-estaoportunidad-que-me-da-defensa-es-muy-importante.html |access-date=1 November 2020 |work=Vavel}}</ref> He made his debut for the ''Halcón'' on 18 September by manager [[Hernán Crespo]] in a 3–0 win over [[Delfín S.C.|Delfín]] in the Copa Libertadores.<ref name="SW1"/><ref>{{Cite web |last=Cantore |first=Alberto |date=24 September 2020 |title=Copa Libertadores. Enzo Fernández: la joya del semillero de River que se lució en Defensa y Justicia |trans-title=Copa Libertadores. Enzo Fernández: the gem from River's youth academy who shone at Defensa y Justicia. |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/deportes/futbol/libertadores-enzo-fernandez-defensa-river-nid2459298/ |access-date=14 April 2025 |website=LA NACION |language=es}}</ref> Despite initially not being a starter, his performances impressed his manager and eventually he earned a place in the team, helping the club win the [[2020 Copa Sudamericana]], starting in the 3–0 win over fellow Argentinian side [[Club Atlético Lanús|Lanús]] in the final, winning his first career title.<ref name=":2" />

====2021–22: First-team breakthrough====
After impressing on loan, Fernández returned to River Plate, during the season at the request of manager Marcelo Gallardo, making his return on 15 July 2021, in the [[2021 Copa Libertadores#Final Satges|first leg of Copa Libertadores round-of-16]], featuring in the 1–1 home draw to fellow Argentinian side [[Argentinos Juniors]].<ref name=":2" /> He immediately became a starter and on 14 August, he scored his first goal for the club and provided an assist in a 2–0 win over [[Club Atlético Vélez Sarsfield|Vélez Sarsfield]] in the Primera División.<ref name=":2" /> On 20 December, he agreed to a contract extension to 2025.<ref>{{cite web |date=20 December 2021 |title=Enzo Fernández renovó hasta 2025 con una cláusula millonaria |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/river-plate/enzo-fernandez-contrato-renovacion-2025_0_QggzG6bFW.html |access-date=14 April 2025 |website=Olé |language=es}}</ref> Following a promising start in the [[2022 Argentine Primera División|2022 season]], which he scored eight goals and provided six assists in 19 games, Fernández was named the best active footballer in [[Argentine Primera División|Argentina]], being subsequently scouted by a number of established European teams.<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{cite web |date=11 April 2022 |title=Enzo Fernández, con el ADN de River, despierta interés en Europa |trans-title=Enzo Fernández, with River's DNA, sparks interest in Europe. |url=https://ar.marca.com/claro/futbol/river-plate/2022/04/11/62543011268e3ecf5e8b4597.html |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220506141634/https://ar.marca.com/claro/futbol/river-plate/2022/04/11/62543011268e3ecf5e8b4597.html |archive-date=6 May 2022 |access-date=30 June 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Tales Torraga – Na mira do Real e da Argentina para a Copa: quem é o novo craque do River |trans-title=Report: Tales Torraga – In the sights of Real Madrid and Argentina for the World Cup: Who is River's new star? |url=https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/colunas/tales-torraga/2022/03/14/na-mira-do-real-e-da-argentina-para-a-copa-quem-e-o-novo-craque-do-river.htm |access-date=14 April 2025 |website=UOL |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=24 April 2022 |title=Enzo Fernández, el que hace jugar y gritar a River |trans-title=Enzo Fernández, el que hace jugar y gritar a River |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/river-plate/enzo-fernandez-jugar-gritar-river_0_phAeyInV49.html}}</ref>

===Benfica===
[[File:Enzo Fernández.jpg|thumb|upright|Fernández with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2022]]

On 23 June 2022, River Plate reached an agreement with [[Primeira Liga]] team [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] for the transfer of Fernández for a €10&nbsp;million fee for 75% of his economic rights plus €8&nbsp;million in add-ons, but with the player remaining at River Plate until the end of the club's [[2022 Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores]] campaign.<ref>{{Cite web |title=OFICIAL: Benfica tem princípio de acordo por Enzo Fernández |trans-title=Official: Benfica has reached a preliminary agreement for Enzo Fernández. |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica/enzo-fernandez/oficial-benfica-tem-principio-de-acordo-por-enzo-fernandez |access-date=14 April 2025 |website=Maisfutebol |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=23 June 2022 |title=Agora é oficial e com moldes diferentes do esperado: Benfica com 'princípio de acordo' para contratar Enzo Fernández |trans-title=Now it's official and with different terms than expected: Benfica with 'preliminary agreement' to sign Enzo Fernández. |url=https://observador.pt/2022/06/23/agora-e-oficial-e-com-moldes-diferentes-do-esperado-benfica-com-principio-de-acordo-para-contratar-enzo-fernandez/ |access-date=30 June 2022 |work=Observador |language=pt}}</ref> Following River Plate's round of 16 exit from the Copa Libertadores, on 14 July, Benfica confirmed the deal,<ref>{{cite news |title=Enzo Fernández is a Benfica player! |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2022/07/14/futebol-benfica-enzo-fernandez-apresentacao-reforco-2022-23 |date=14 July 2022 |access-date=14 April 2025 |publisher=S.L. Benfica}}</ref> giving Fernández the number 13 shirt, previously worn by club legend [[Eusébio]].<ref>{{cite news |date=14 July 2022 |title=Eusébio 'Ajudou' Enzo Fernández A Escolher O Número |trans-title=Eusébio 'Helped' Enzo Fernández Choose the Number. |url=https://www.abola.pt/amp/2022-07-14/benfica-eusebio-ajudou-enzo-fernandez-a-escolher-o-numero/949430 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220717182101/https://www.abola.pt/amp/2022-07-14/benfica-eusebio-ajudou-enzo-fernandez-a-escolher-o-numero/949430 |archive-date=17 July 2022 |access-date=15 July 2022 |work=A Bola |language=pt}}</ref>

He made his debut for the club on 2 August, scoring his first goal for the club, a half-volley from outside the penalty area, in a 4–1 home win over [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] in the first leg of the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round|2022–23 UEFA Champions League third qualifying round]]. He then scored in Benfica's next matches: a 4–0 home win over [[F.C. Arouca|Arouca]] in the [[Primeira Liga]], and a 3–1 away win over Midtjylland in the second leg of the UEFA Champions League third qualifying round.<ref>{{cite news |date=9 August 2022 |title=Enzo Fernández e o hygge à Benfica |trans-title=Enzo Fernández and the hygge at Benfica. |url=https://tribuna.expresso.pt/benfica/2022-08-09-Enzo-Fernandez-e-o-hygge-a-Benfica-c8e90a4d |access-date=23 December 2022 |work=Tribuna Expresso |language=pt}}</ref> His impressive performances continued throughout the month and following a run of five consecutive wins and three clean sheets, he was named the Primeira Liga's Midfielder of the Month,<ref>{{cite news |date=8 September 2022 |title=Melhores de agosto: Enzo Fernández é o Médio do Mês da Liga Portugal bwin |trans-title=Best of August: Enzo Fernández is the Midfielder of the Month in Liga Portugal bwin. |url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20222023/noticias/geral/premios-mensais/agosto/melhores-de-agosto-enzo-fernandez-e-o-medio-do-mes-da-liga-portugal-bwin/ |access-date=9 September 2022 |publisher=Liga Portugal |language=pt}}</ref> a feat which was repeated for the months of October and November.<ref name="MFAward">{{cite news |date=15 December 2022 |title=Melhores de outubro/novembro: Enzo distinguido com o Prémio VITO Médio do Mês da Liga Portugal bwin |trans-title=Best of October/November: Enzo awarded the VITO Midfielder of the Month Award in Liga Portugal bwin. |url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20222023/noticias/geral/premios-mensais/outubronovembro/melhores-de-outubronovembro-enzo-distinguido-com-o-premio-vito-medio-do-mes-da-liga-portugal-bwin/ |access-date=23 December 2022 |publisher=Liga Portugal |language=pt}}</ref>

===Chelsea===
[[File:F20250713AH-1313 President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania Trump attend the FIFA Club World Cup Final soccer match.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Enzo Fernández taking a kick at the start of the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup final|FIFA Club World Cup final]].]]

Following Fernández's success internationally at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], he was linked with a move to [[Premier League]] teams [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]<ref>{{cite web |last=Meade |first=Samuel |date=20 December 2022 |title=Liverpool transfer target Fernandez has club preference ahead of January window |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/liverpool-enzo-fernandez-transfer-latest-28775494 |access-date=14 April 2025 |website=Daily Mirror}}</ref> in the January 2023 transfer window, however, Benfica were adamant he wouldn't be sold for less than his €121m release clause.<ref>{{cite news |last=Steinberg |first=Jacob |date=23 January 2023 |title=Chelsea plan renewed push to sign Enzo Fernández from Benfica |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/jan/23/chelsea-enzo-fernandez-benfica |access-date=14 April 2025 |work=The Guardian |issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{cite news |title=Enzo Fernandez: Chelsea sign midfielder in £106.8m British-record transfer deal from Benfica |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11668/12799395/enzo-fernandez-to-chelsea-blues-agree-premier-league-record-105m-transfer-deal-for-benfica-midfielder |access-date=1 February 2023 |website=Sky Sports}}</ref> After negotiations lasting some ten hours and led by CFC co-owner [[Behdad Eghbali]], the two clubs, on 31 January 2023, the last day of the Premier League's transfer window, came to an agreement and Fernández signed an eight-and-a-half-year contract, valid until 2031, with Chelsea, whose financial package reportedly was worth a total of £106.8 million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Chelsea transfer news: Fernandez transfers to Chelsea |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/fernandez-transfers-to-chelsea |date=1 February 2023 |access-date=14 April 2025 |publisher=Chelsea F.C.}}</ref>  The transfer fee paid by Chelsea was, at the time, a [[List of most expensive association football transfers|British-record transfer deal]]. Benfica received an initial £30 million installment that will be followed by five more.<ref>{{cite news |date=1 February 2023 |title=Chelsea sign Benfica's Fernandez for record fee |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37635969/chelsea-sign-enzo-fernandez-benfica-meeting-120m-release-clause-sources |access-date=14 April 2025 |website=ESPN}}</ref><ref name=":3" />

Fernández made his debut in the [[Premier League]] on 3 February in a [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|home]] goal-less draw against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]], playing the full game.<ref>{{cite web |last=O'Halloran |first=Connor |date=3 February 2023 |title=Chelsea's attacking woe vs. Fulham overshadows bright debut by record signee Enzo Fernandez |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37636066/chelsea-attacking-woes-continue-enzo-fernandez-debut |access-date=14 April 2025 |website=ESPN}}</ref> On 11 February, he registered an assist for the team's only goal in a 1–1 league draw at [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64520927 |title=West Ham United 1–1 Chelsea |first=Neil |last=Johnston |website=BBC Sport |date=11 February 2023 |access-date=11 February 2023}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Chelsea in a 2–1 win over [[AFC Wimbledon]] in the second round of the [[2023–24 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] on 30 August 2023.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/report-chelsea-2-afc-wimbledon-1 |title=Report: Chelsea 2–1 AFC Wimbledon |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |date=30 August 2023 |access-date=25 October 2023}}</ref> He scored his first Premier League goals on 3 December, by netting a [[Brace (association football)|brace]] in a 3–2 home victory over [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Match report: Chelsea 3 Brighton 2 |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/match-report-chelsea-3-brighton-2 |access-date=14 April 2025 |publisher=Chelsea F.C.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Meade |first=Samuel |date=20 December 2022 |title=Liverpool transfer target Fernandez has club preference ahead of January window |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/liverpool-enzo-fernandez-transfer-latest-28775494 |access-date=14 April 2025 |website=Daily Mirror}}</ref>

On 28 May 2025, Fernández scored Chelsea's opening goal in a 4–1 victory over [[Real Betis]] in the [[2025 UEFA Conference League final|Conference League final]], helping them become the first team to have won all four major European competitions.<ref>{{cite news |last=Keble |first=Alex |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4322307 |title=Conference League champions! Chelsea win thrilling final 4–1 |publisher=Premier League |date=28 May 2025|access-date=20 May 2026 }}</ref> Six weeks later, he started in Chelsea's 3–0 victory over [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] in the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup final]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.sky.com/story/chelsea-win-fifa-club-world-cup-with-victory-over-psg-as-donald-trump-watches-from-stands-13396284 |title=Chelsea win FIFA Club World Cup with victory over PSG – as Donald Trump presents trophy |publisher=Sky News |date=13 July 2025 }}</ref>

On 31 January 2026, on his 150th appearance for Chelsea, Fernández scored in the second minute of injury time to secure a 3–2 win over West Ham after the home team was 0-2 down at half-time.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Enzo Fernández seals thrilling Chelsea fightback to shatter 10-man West Ham|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/jan/31/chelsea-west-ham-premier-league-match-report|work=The Guardian|date=31 January 2026|access-date=20 May 2026|issn=0261-3077|language=en-GB|first=Jacob|last=Steinberg}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Enzo Fernandez: How Argentine midfielder has become key for Chelsea|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c1lz14ydr1go|website=BBC Sport|date=31 January 2026|access-date=20 May 2026|language=en-GB|first=Nizaar|last=Kinsella}}</ref> Later that year, on 26 April, he scored the only goal in a 1–0 win over [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]], securing the club's 17th appearance in an [[2026 FA Cup final|FA Cup final]].<ref>{{cite web |last=McNulty |first=Phil |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c62kj76yk43t |title=Chelsea 1–0 Leeds United |publisher=BBC Sport |date=26 April 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Enzo Fernández WC2022.jpg|thumb|upright|Fernández with [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]]]

On 24 July 2019, Fernández was selected by the [[Argentina national under-18 football team|Argentina U18s]] manager [[Esteban Solari]] to represent his nation at the [[2019 COTIF Tournament]] in Spain.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ghazal |first=Nadir |date=2019-07-19 |title=Con Enzo Fernández entre los posibles citados, la Sub 18 defenderá el Torneo de L'Alcúdia |url=https://lapaginamillonaria.com/riverplate/River-con-Enzo-Fernandez-entre-los-posibles-citados-la-Sub-18-defendera-el-Torneo-de-LAlcudia-Seleccion-Argentina-20190719-0005.html |access-date=2025-04-14 |website=La Página Millonaria |language=es-AR}}</ref> On 3 November 2021, he was called up by [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]] manager [[Lionel Scaloni]] for two [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] and [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]].<ref name=":2" /> He made his senior team debut on 24 September 2022, by coming on as a 64th-minute substitute for [[Leandro Paredes]] in a 3–0 win against [[Honduras national football team|Honduras]].<ref>{{cite web |date=24 September 2022 |title=Messi bisa na estreia de Enzo Fernández |trans-title=Messi scores a brace in Enzo Fernández's debut. |url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2022-09-24/messi-bisa-na-estreia-de-enzo-fernandez/957941 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221206073724/https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2022-09-24/messi-bisa-na-estreia-de-enzo-fernandez/957941 |archive-date=6 December 2022 |access-date=24 September 2022 |language=pt}}</ref> On 11 November, he was named in Argentina's 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |date=11 November 2022 |title=Lista de la Selección Argentina para el Mundial de Qatar 2022 |trans-title=Argentina's Squad List for the 2022 Qatar World Cup. |url=https://www.tycsports.com/seleccion-argentina/lista-seleccion-argentina-mundial-de-qatar-2022-id476596.html |access-date=11 November 2022 |website=[[TyC Sports]] |language=es}}</ref> After coming on for [[Guido Rodríguez]] in the 57th minute, on 26 November, Fernández scored his first international goal, closing Argentina's 2–0 group stage win against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Brownsell |first=Joseph Stepansky,Dorian Geiger,Rohan Sharma,James |title=Argentina vs Mexico 2–0: World Cup 2022 – as it happened |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/liveblog/2022/11/26/live-argentina-vs-mexico-world-cup |access-date=2025-04-14 |website=Al Jazeera |language=en}}</ref> In doing so, he became the second youngest player ever (only behind [[Lionel Messi]]) to score a World Cup goal for Argentina at 21 years, ten months and thirteen days old. On 3 December, he achieved a rather not so famous record, becoming the youngest own goal scorer in the history of Argentina in the FIFA World Cup, in the round of sixteen match against [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]], when his attempt to block [[Craig Goodwin]]'s shot deflected into his team's net as Argentina beat Australia 2–1.<ref>{{Cite news|first1=Andrew |last1=Cawthorne |first2=William |last2=Schomberg|url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/messi-helps-argentina-past-australia-into-world-cup-quarter-finals-2022-12-03/ |title=Messi helps Argentina past Australia into World Cup quarter-finals |website=[[Reuters]] |date=3 December 2022 |access-date=8 December 2022}}</ref> After defeating [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] 3–0 in the semi-final, Fernández played in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup Final|final]] against [[France national football team|France]], where Argentina won the World Cup by a score of 4–2 on penalties after a 3–3 draw.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/match-centre/match/17/255711/285077/400128145?country=DE&wtw-filter=ALL |title=Argentina 3–3 France (Argentina wins 4–2 on penalties) |publisher=FIFA |date=18 December 2022 }}</ref> He was named the [[FIFA World Cup Young Player Award|best young player of the tournament]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-18 |title=Argentina's Enzo Fernandez wins World Cup 2022 Young Player of the Tournament |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/argentina-enzo-fernandez-wins-world-cup-2022-young-player-of-the-tournament/bltba0a9699be0f0238 |access-date=2025-04-14 |website=www.goal.com |language=en}}</ref>

In June 2024, Fernández was called up to represent Argentina at the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Copa America 2024: Enzo returns as Argentina advance |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/copa-america-2024-enzo-returns-as-argentina-advance |access-date=2025-04-14 |website=www.chelseafc.com |language=en-gb}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/nomina-de-futbolistas-convocados-para-disputar-la-copa-america-2026-en-estados-unidos |title=Nómina de futbolistas convocados por Lionel Scaloni para disputar la Copa América 2024 en Estados Unidos |trans-title=List of footballers called by Lionel Scaloni to compete in the 2024 Copa América in the United States |publisher=Argentine Football Association |date=15 June 2024 |language=es}}</ref> He played in all but one of their matches and recorded two assists as they went on to win the tournament, defeating [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] 1–0 in the [[2024 Copa América final|final]] and earning him his second senior international trophy.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lynch |first=Peter |date=2024-07-15 |title=Adrian reacts after Alexis Mac Allister wins the Copa America with Argentina |url=https://www.rousingthekop.com/2024/07/15/adrian-reacts-after-alexis-mac-allister-wins-the-copa-america-with-argentina/ |access-date=2025-04-14 |website=Rousing The Kop |language=en-GB}}</ref>

===July 2024 video controversy===
{{see also|2024 Copa América#Argentine celebrations|2024 Copa América final#Argentina team celebrations}}
In July 2024, following Argentina's Copa América triumph, a video showing Fernández and other Argentinian players chanting alleged racist chants about the origin of France national team players on the team bus surfaced, which led to outrage and criticism from the [[French Football Federation]] (FFF) and French sports minister [[Amélie Oudéa-Castéra]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=France condemns Argentina footballers' 'racist remarks' – DW – 07/16/2024 |url=https://www.dw.com/en/france-condemns-argentina-footballers-racist-remarks/a-69684417 |access-date=2025-04-14 |website=dw.com |language=en}}</ref> Several of Fernández's French teammates at Chelsea proceeded to unfollow him on [[Instagram]] and made posts on [[Twitter]] showing their anger,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pulsesports.ng/football/story/racism-storm-rocks-chelsea-as-players-unfollow-enzo-fernandez-on-instagram-2024071708135434477|title=Racism storm rocks Chelsea as players UNFOLLOW Enzo Fernández on Instagram|work=Pulse Sports Nigeria|date=17 July 2024|author=Ifeanyi Ufomadu|access-date=18 July 2024}}</ref> which led to Fernández apologising through Instagram. The FFF lodged a complaint to [[FIFA]] about the remarks,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/sport/20240717-fifa-launches-probe-into-racist-and-homophobic-chants-by-argentina-players|title=FIFA launches probe into racist and homophobic chants by Argentina players|date=17 July 2024|website=France 24|access-date=18 July 2024}}</ref> while Chelsea announced that it had "instigated an internal disciplinary procedure".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/club-statement-july-17-2024|title=Club statement|publisher=Chelsea Football Club|date=17 July 2024|access-date=18 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c80x1947rxzo|title=Fernandez faces disciplinary action over alleged racist chant|work=BBC Sport|date=17 July 2024|access-date=18 July 2024}}</ref> After offering a private apology to his Chelsea teammates and a donation to an anti-discrimination charity, Chelsea announced that they would not be taking any disciplinary actions against Fernández.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Aarons |first=Ed |date=2024-07-30 |title=Chelsea take no action against Enzo Fernández after charity donation |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/jul/30/chelsea-take-no-action-against-enzo-fernandez-charity-racist-song |access-date=2025-04-14 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

==Style of play==
[[File:Argentina vs mexico enzofernandez.jpg|thumb|right|Fernández playing for Argentina at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]. Fernández has been noted for his ability to break up play and recycle possession.|253x253px]]
A versatile midfielder, Fernández usually plays as a [[deep-lying playmaker]], responsible for breaking up play, dictating the tempo, and recycling possession, but he is also a capable [[attacking midfielder|attacking-midfielder]]. Although he prefers operating centrally, he can be seen occupying the left half-space assisted by a defensive midfield partner, like his former Benfica team-mate, [[Florentino Luís]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Analytical look at Chelsea's record signing, Enzo Fernández |url=https://weaintgotnohistory.sbnation.com/2023/2/9/23592318/analytical-look-at-chelseas-record-signing-enzo-fernandez |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230209180255/https://weaintgotnohistory.sbnation.com/2023/2/9/23592318/analytical-look-at-chelseas-record-signing-enzo-fernandez |archive-date=9 February 2023 |date=9 Feb 2023 |work=We Ain't Got No History |last=Connolly |first=Martin}}</ref>

Fernández plays quick short passes, accurate long passes, and lobbed balls. He is combative in his midfield duels, protects spaces and his backline efficiently, and possesses good passing range and vision. He can dribble into dangerous territory or out of it. He thrives in receiving the ball in tight spaces and is press-resistant. He is adept at breaking defensive lines with his passes, playing through balls, as well as recycling possession in the midfield. Out of possession, Fernández looks to proactively disrupt opposition attack, anticipate and intercept passes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Enzo Fernandez analysis: Benfica's creative prodigy taking Europe by storm |url=https://www.foottheball.com/players-in-focus/enzo-fernandez-stats-profile-river-plate-scout-report-transfer-news-analysis-potential/|date=18 September 2022|access-date=4 Feb 2023 |archive-date=9 February 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230209221433/https://www.foottheball.com/players-in-focus/enzo-fernandez-stats-profile-chelsea-scout-report-transfer-news-analysis-potential/ |website=foottheball.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://analyticsfc.co.uk/blog/2022/08/18/scouting-the-primeira-liga-the-next-players-to-make-the-step-up/|title=Scouting the Primeira Liga: The Next Players to Make the Step Up|date=18 August 2022|access-date=19 October 2022 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230209222200/https://analyticsfc.co.uk/blog/2022/08/18/scouting-the-primeira-liga-the-next-players-to-make-the-step-up/ |archive-date=9 February 2023 |website=analyticsfc.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/enzo-fernandez-the-future-of-argentina-and-benficas-midfield/|title=Enzo Fernandez – The Future Of Argentina and Benfica's Midfield?|date=11 August 2022|access-date=19 October 2022 |archive-date=9 February 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230209222233/https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/enzo-fernandez-the-future-of-argentina-and-benficas-midfield/ |website=breakingthelines.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://themastermindsite.com/2022/10/10/analyzing-three-of-europes-most-promising-central-midfielders/|title=Analyzing three of Europe's most promising central midfielders|date=10 October 2022|access-date=19 October 2022 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230209222316/https://themastermindsite.com/2022/10/10/analyzing-three-of-europes-most-promising-central-midfielders/ |archive-date=9 February 2023 |website=themastermindsite.com}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Fernández is named after three-time [[Copa América]] winner and former River Plate player [[Enzo Francescoli]], due to his father Raúl's fascination with the Uruguayan. In an interview, he said that his favourite player is Lionel Messi.<ref name=":1" />

Fernández was married to fellow Argentine Valentina Cervantes, with whom he has a daughter, born on 4 March 2020. On 26 October 2023, their son was born.<ref>{{cite news |date=23 December 2022 |title=Enzo Fernández y su emoción ante la sorpresa de su esposa y su hija: "Orgullosa de todo lo que lograste" |trans-title=Enzo Fernández and his emotion upon the surprise from his wife and daughter: "Proud of everything you've achieved." |url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/enzo-fernandez-emocion-sorpresa-esposa-hija-orgullosa-lograste-_0_8C22ScCmjX.html |access-date=26 December 2022 |work=[[Clarín (Argentine newspaper)|Clarín]] |language=es}}</ref>

On 31 October 2024, Cervantes announced on her Instagram story that she and Fernández were separating, writing (translated from Spanish) "Enzo and I have decided to take some distance from each other today. But we will always be family, and we will support each other in everything, because there are two children involved who need a lot of love from us. I know the person Enzo is, what an excellent father he is, and what heart he has. And that is enough for me. Please don't try to create conflicts where there are none."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/enzo-fernandez-wife-separation-chelsea-star-heartbreaking-instagram-post/blt1a772c9d4accedb5#cs63f0f3a9e16c8484|title=Enzo Fernandez's wife confirms separation from Chelsea star in heartbreaking Instagram post|date=31 October 2024|website=goal.com|access-date=2 November 2024}}</ref>

Argentine journalist Julieta Argenta provided further details on the split claiming "He told her he wants to live a life on his own. They're still a family and he feels the need to experience the stage he skipped by choosing family early on."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/chelsea-2024-11-01-argentine-journalist-reveals-what-really-caused-the-break-up-of-enzo-fernandez-and-his-ch/|title=Argentine journalist reveals what really caused the break up of Enzo Fernandez and his childhood love|date=1 November 2024|website=tribuna.com|access-date=2 November 2024}}</ref>

===Driving infractions===
On 11 September 2024, Fernández was disqualified from driving for six months,<ref name=":4">{{Cite web |date=11 September 2024 |title=Chelsea's Fernández gets 6-month driving ban |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/41220642/chelsea-enzo-fernandez-driving-ban-wales |access-date=20 May 2026|website=[[ESPN]] |language=en}}</ref> receiving a 12-point penalty and being fined £3,020, following two driving offences committed in Wales in November and December 2023 by the driver of a [[Porsche Cayenne]] of which Fernández was registered as the owner.<ref name=":4" />

The car was caught by [[Dyfed-Powys Police]] running a red light on Church Street, [[Llanelli]] on 28 November 2023, and then caught by [[South Wales Police]], a few weeks later, on 20 December, speeding on Carmarthen Road, [[Swansea]]. The two police agencies sent officers with court papers to Fernández’s home address in Kingston-Upon-Thames and to Chelsea’s training ground in [[Stoke D'Abernon]], [[Surrey]] to identify the driver of the Porsche but Fernández failed to appear for the hearings at Llanelli Magistrates' Court. He was charged £1,000 and £110 in police costs for the offence in Llanelli and a further £1,000 charge, £800 in victim surcharge, and £110 in police costs for the offence in Swansea.<ref name=":5" /> Fernández received 12 penalty points (6 for each offence), which on top of 9 existing penalty points for speeding led to a six-month ban from driving.<ref name=":5">{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/13213066/enzo-fernandez-chelsea-and-argentina-midfielder-handed-six-month-driving-ban-fined-gbp3-020-and-given-12-point-penalty|title=Enzo Fernandez: Chelsea and Argentina midfielder handed six-month driving ban, fined £3,020 and given 12-point penalty|date=12 September 2024|website=[[Sky Sports]]|access-date=20 May 2026}}</ref>

